Review: This is a pretty good and fast alternative to using a Swiffer duster or car cleaning wipes. This picked up the amount of dust that had collected the past year for me (I don't really drive, so not much dust). It's easy to use, grips well, you can see the dust collected on the gel. If you have a lot of dust, debris, crumbs galore, do not use this product first! This is not meant for cleaning really grimy cars. This is great for light layers, when you notice dust collecting. I agree with another reviewer saying it doesn't get into the vents very well, but if you have small enough fingers, it's easy to work the gel in between the slats. Also, do not store in the glove box. Think about it: your car is out in direct sunlight, facing the elements within your microclimate, so your car will heat up or cool down which will deteriorate the gel overtime even if stored in the glove box. Keep this somewhere inside your home, away from small children.
This product did a great job of cleaning things I normally can't get to. It's very sticky for the first use but does lose some after the initial use. But overall great value for your money.

This stuff is a must have for me, it didn't take long to find this helpful and convenient to use. When I am finished driving for the day, routine is to take an extra 45 seconds and absorb all the dust, dirt, ashes, etc. from my dash and center console.I definitely ordered two more for on deck, and I feel, depending, that one of these gel slime will last a solid two months before it gets too grimy.Great case it stores in, which prolongs the use and just very convenient to store in car somewhere... preferably not in sunlight.As I mentioned, it is a slime type of gel, so with heavy use there is a extremely light residue left behind. But honestly it really is not an issue in even the least. Also if I very lightly absorb particles, the residue is pretty much non existent.I recommend highly for any surface tidying up you need, and hard to reach places. In a very slight way, this is a game changer.

I pruchased this to use in my vehicle to get into those hard to clean areas. I ended up using it in my dad's work truck to really put it to the test. He is working in a very dusty area with the red dirt....his truck was covered in the thick dust, so a perfect test of the product. He and I cleaned what we could with rags, but I wanted to try this stuff out on the creases and vents. It worked alright. Here are the pros/cons of the product from my initial test:Pros:- Ease of use: This is very easy to use. Just open it up, pull it out, and start dabbing it into the dusty areas. I found that tapping the dust to get the worst of it off before dragging it over a second time worked best.- Cleaning: This is good for loose dust. It worked really well at removing the dust in the vents and some of the corners you could not get a rag into.Cons:- Cleaning: This did not remove some of the stuck on dust that a rag would have removed. I also found that getting in tighter crevices did not work very well either. It also left a little greasy feel that may attract dust or that some people may not like on their dashes or inside their vehicles.- Cleaning the product: With as heavy of dust that was in my dad's truck, the gel got pretty dirty. I am not sure the best way to clean it, or if you can even clean it. Rags and towels are easy...just throw them into a washing machine. I'm guessing this is use until completely dirty and throw away.- Messy: This also leaves a greasy feel to your hands. With rags, you can usually minimize this, but this stuff gets all over your fingers, especially the finger you use to press it into vents.Overall, this is something that is a neat idea, but it really is not great. It worked okay at getting loose dirt and dust off of surfaces, but you could also get the same results from using something like tape or wrapping a small tool with some cloth and using cleaning agents. This might make a cheap, fun stocking stuffer if you want to get something that is different. Personally, I don't think I'll buy this again and just use rags.

This magic goop is so handy I really can’t even tell you how nice it is. If you’ve ever had those nooks and cranny’s you can’t reach no matter how hard you try, now you can. Picks up dirt dust and grime so well. It’s fairly easy to clean and 100% capable of reusing depending on hot well it’s still picking up. Once you notice it isn’t picking up anymore, toss it and get you another. While I use this as a car detailer, this would even be great for those that like to keep their cars tidy or parents with kids who know how to make a mess everywhere. Highly recommend!

There are many options for an automatic tire inflator, this one just fit every need for me.  It’s accurate, easy to use, quick and compact to store in the car.  The fully charged lithium battery can inflate two slightly under inflated car tires before having to be recharged.  Not great, but it will get you going in a pinch. Avg value for cost.  Yes, it’s loud, but not that bad. Bottom line…it works!

I tested it today and was pleased with it. It is small. The controls are easy to use and it has multiple modes (Car, motorcycle, sports equipment, custom). It charges via USB which is convenient since I'll keep it in my truck. I found my right front tire low this morning and set it to add 6 lbs. of pressure (it has auto-cutoff!). It worked fine - about 1 lb. per minute. This beats having nothing in an out of the way place if you find yourself down 15 lbs. It also has an LED light at the top. I'll probably get one for my Harley.

I used the Airmoto Tire Inflator right away to put air in my car tires, and it worked just as expected. The device is easy to use, and the built-in tire pressure gauge is a handy feature that helped me keep track of the exact pressure. It's portable and works well for inflating car, motorcycle, and bicycle tires.The only suggestion I have for improvement is that the hose where you attach the compressor to the tire could be longer or positioned differently. Since it dangles when you use it, especially on car tires, it would be better if it could sit closer to the ground for stability during inflation.Overall, it’s a reliable and compact air pump that gets the job done!

I was able to use it to blow up a flat car tire from 6 psi to 31.5 psi before it died. Mind you that was on the charge that it came with straight out of the box. I am sure it would do even better had I had the chance to charge it up first. I was then able to get it to the shop to have the tire changed since it had a nail in it. This device is very small, which is very convenient, and it blew up the tire in about 15 minutes. It will do the job and is great for emergencies.

It's a great little pump. I used it to top off my tires when the temperature changed here in Minnesota, and the pressure in the tires dropped a bit.  As others noted, the battery life is not fantastic, but it works.  I could top off four tires on my SUV (275/65R18) from 30 PSI to 33 PSI but I had to charge it to get the last one PSI on the 4th tire.  Those tires have a lot of volume, so I would expect it would work better on smaller tires.  It does recharge quickly.Will be nice to have in the car in the event I am not near a source of air.

I recently purchased the NOCO Boost Plus GB40, and it has been an absolute lifesaver. This compact and powerful jump starter is a must-have for any vehicle owner.Reliable Performance: The NOCO Boost Plus GB40 has consistently delivered reliable performance. It quickly jump-starts my car, even in freezing temperatures, without any issues. It's incredibly reassuring to have this dependable device on hand for emergencies.Compact and Portable: Despite its powerful performance, the GB40 is surprisingly compact and easy to carry. It fits perfectly in my glove compartment or backpack, making it convenient to take on road trips or keep in the car for unexpected situations.Versatile Features: Beyond jump-starting, the GB40 has versatile features. It can charge smartphones, tablets, and other USB devices, making it a multi-purpose tool. The USB charging port is fast and efficient.  Even has a flashlight if neededOverall, the NOCO Boost Plus GB40 is a fantastic investment for anyone looking for a reliable, compact, and versatile jump starter. It's a product that delivers peace of mind and convenience. Highly recommend!

I cannot say enough good things about this jumper.  I have used it twice so far and my car fired up immediately when I put this jumper on it.  It holds it charge well.  It is small and easy to use.  Charging is simple.  I would recommend this device to anyone that just wants to have something around for peace of mind or to help out others if they need a jump.  It will easily fit in a glove box or in a small trunk space.

Tried it out on "spare" vehicle. Doesn't get driven much so always completely dead when we go to use it. New battery so...  put jump starter on (husband had me do it myself so I'd know how to use it) and went straight to start vehicle. Started with no hesitation,  immediately. Now we are fighting over whose car we are going to keep it in and we may buy another. Takes alot to impress me and I was very impressed. Also has light so you can see in dark, and can charge cell phone etc

Okay it’s not that important but this device is absolutely amazing and it should be included in every preparation/emergency kit. I was having trouble with my truck battery, and I order this and received it same day. It was completely dead and would not even attempt turning over. I hooked it up to this jumper kit and I was immediately able to turn on my truck and drive it to the store to buy a new battery. I am a delivery driver and I feel so relieved having this device on me just in case another battery mishap happens mid delivery lol.I love the multiple features it brings to the table in such a compact size it could almost fit in your pocket. I am going to buy a couple more of these eventually to give to my older sisters. Every battery dies and unfortunately you don’t get to choose where you are what you’re doing when it does. I would much rather them have this handy, easy to use, no help required device then asking for help god knows where. If you are on the fence with this one, SEND IT

I would love to give this 5-stars, and I would if I were only reviewing its performance.Overall, this product does exactly what is says it will do. The quality is good, its sturdy, and the carrying pouch is just OK (Hate the pouch).However, the battery leads are too short for some applications.If you are connecting this to a battery with easy access you are golden. One of the uses I have is to occasionally jump start a 5K generator and the battery is not easily accessible. Do not misunderstand me, I can connect the cables from this unit to the generator battery terminals. But the cable is so short it is difficult to plug the cable into the jump starter.  What I end up doing is first connect the cable to the battery, then get the jump starter close enough to plug the cable into it. Next comes a little balancing act, as if I do not hold it in place the cable will drop out of the jump starter.I have a few NOCO products, and they all work well. Big fan!But come on NOCO, for applications like mine the short cable is infuriating. An extra couple of inches of cable would make this jump starter perfect.Last thing:Battery Cable - Too shortJump Starter - works great, compact, easily stored, ruggedStorage Bag - Hate it! will be putting into a small caseMy Use Cases - Jump Generator, Jump Started a 2022 Chevy Truck with 5.7L V-8, Jump Started stranded car

I tried this gel on dirty electronic peripherals and the console of my vehicle. It is completely good at picking up dust from smooth hard plastic surfaces and pretty good at getting gritty crumbs out from the bottom of cupholders. Its main advantage over cleaning wipes is the ability to be pressed into the small gaps in computer keyboards and other odd dusty areas as shown in my video. The material picked up adheres to the gel and can then be folded or kneaded into the blob to keep a fresh surface for cleaning. It's basically reusable as long as it's stored in the jar with a tight lid out of hot areas. I deducted one star because it cannot be stored in the car for quick cleanups or in a warm summer garage where it will essentially melt to an unusable consistency. It's not a perfect cleaning tool but it does a pretty good job where other tools cannot fit into tight spaces. It is sort of fun to use because the color, texture, and function remind me of a blob in a science fiction movie from back in the day.

As soon as I opened the package I thought I've seen this slimy stuff before.  It is almost exactly like the green slime played with and if the slime got dirty (which was very easy to do) was ruined.  They basically changed the color and reverse marketed it.Stuff works great at picking up dust and small particles without any problem and it doesn't leave a sticky residue.

Only works well on hard  SMOOTH  plastic surfaces.  If hard textured surface sometimes leaves sticky residue behind and does not pick up all dust.  Not useful for softer surfaces ( as I expected).  I useful for limited surfaces in the car.

The AstroAI Tire Inflator Portable Air Compressor is a lifesaver! This compact pump has quickly become one of my favorite car accessories. It’s small enough to keep in the trunk but powerful enough to get the job done fast. The digital pressure gauge makes it easy to get precise pressure, and the emergency LED light is incredibly useful for nighttime or low-visibility situations. I’ve used it for everything from topping off car tires to inflating bike tires and  – it’s so versatile!Plus, it only takes minutes to inflate a car tire to the exact pressure. The 12V DC connection works great with my car, and the pump automatically shuts off once it hits the desired pressure, so I don’t have to worry about overinflation.Highly recommend this to anyone looking for a reliable, multi-purpose air compressor!

I've had a Slime Home Air Station (120 volt only) for many years, but the hose recently failed and couldn't be repaired, so it was time to find a replacement. This piece meets the need. It seems well-made and comes with a useful User Manual. However, it IS quite different from what I had before.First off, it's 12 volt only, via a standard auto 12V  socket. The User Manual said to start the car's engine while using it, so I'm guessing it draws a fair amount of current and might flatten your battery with prolonged use. The inflator hose is also much shorter than what I was used to, but still long enough to reach the valve-stem at the 12 o'clock position while the compressor remains on the ground. It's a bonus that it stays put when it's running and doesn't skate across the surface, as my old unit did.The built-in digital pressure gauge is easy to read, but reads about 2.5 PSI over actual pressure as checked by a separate calibrated  pressure gauge. Actual 35 PSI reads 37.5 PSI on this unit. Not really a big deal. If you can make change, you can do the math.The best feature is the Auto-stop at a preset pressure. My old unit did not have this, so I had to stare at the gauge for several minutes as the needle slowly crept up the dial. On this one, just set the desired pressure and start the compressor. The digital pressure gauge shows inflation progress 0.5 PSI at a time. When it hits the preset setting, it shuts off within a few seconds. My car has 235/55ZR20 tires and this unit will raise the pressure from 32 PSI to 38 PSI in about 3 minutes; not as fast as having a tank-type 120 volt 150 PSI compressor, but certainly acceptable for an occasional-use compact 12 volt unit. I paid less than $30 for this one with next day delivery, so I think qualifies as a great value. Highly recommended.

I recently purchased this small compressor, and overall, I’m quite satisfied with its performance. It’s lightweight, compact, and very easy to use. The long cord is a big plus, allowing me to connect it easily and move around my Jeep. The pressure indicator seems accurate, which is a critical feature when inflating tires.Pros:Lightweight and compact design makes it easy to store and handle.Long cord provides excellent reach, especially for larger vehicles like a Jeep.Accurate pressure indicator for reliable readings.Cons:The connector occasionally slips out of the cigarette lighter socket during use, which can be a bit annoying.After about 10 minutes of use, the connector and hose become quite hot, which might raise durability concerns with prolonged operation.Real-world performance:I tested the compressor on my Jeep's 225/65R17 tires, inflating them from 19 PSI to 35 PSI. Each tire took about 4–5 minutes to inflate. After an off-road trip, it took approximately 20 minutes to restore all four tires to road-ready pressure. While this isn't lightning-fast, it’s efficient enough for the occasional off-road enthusiast.Overall:This compressor is a solid choice for light to moderate use, especially for off-roaders or anyone needing a portable option. A few minor issues aside, it gets the job done reliably.

I don’t typically leave reviews. But this item has saved me a lot of time, hassle, and money. I love that all you have to do is set the psi and it automatically shuts off. Fills fairly quick. I’m very happy with this purchase! The only (slight) cons are: it only has a lighter plug, no wall plug, and you have to be quick when you remove the air hose. Otherwise you’ll seep air out of your tire quick. Other than that, it’s a great product.

I thought that the 12v power cord and the air hose itself was too short to reach the rear wheels of a vehicle. I expressed this design oversight to the seller. They offered me compensation for my inconvenience. I am very pleased with their most excellent customer service and concern with my overall satisfaction. With that said, this is a very decent and adequate emergency air pump to keep in your car. It is compact and easy to use. It has a built in air gauge that helps you pump your tire to a precise pressure. I recommend everyone carry a device like this for road side emergencies.

I had a previous AirTag case that was black but two of them ended up randomly breaking off randomly over time from the small screws falling out. This has a smart silicone/plastic twist case system that makes them basically impossible to fall out or get wet. Great product for the price.
These are fantastic.  Great quality and durable.  We bought them to hide in our luggage during an international trip, they worked great.
Loved the variety of colors, sturdy so far and great price.
easy to take apart for the air tag.  fits perfectly.
Seems to protect well. I like the water resistance and dirt resistance feature. It seems to cushion pretty well.

I’m probably like you, and figured, yeah, they say it’s going to do all these great things and it’ll probably not work anywhere near as advertised. Oh boy was I wrong about that.This product is quite frankly amazing. It’s very easy to use and doesn’t take hours and hours. Everything you need is in the kit except masking tape, which I would highly recommend you use to tape off the perimeter of your light so you don’t get any of the coating on your car paint or accidentally hit it with the sand paper.You first use the oxidizer remover, wipe and clean that off, then you go to the 1000 and 2000 grit sanding discs. Get a good spray bottle with nice clean water, keep the headlight wet while you’re sanding it because basically what you’re doing is wet sanding the surface. You can actually feel the sandpaper, engaging the scratches, and when you finally have a nice smooth, feel to it, spray it down and wipe it off and clean it with a microfiber cloth. Then apply the coating. When you apply the coating, it is literally a miracle. How perfect and clean and clear the lens becomes. It looks brand freaking new!I literally was walking around the garage looking at it saying “damn that looks good“, damn that looks good! You will not be disappointed. This is one of the best products to come around in a long, long time and is worth every penny. I even had a little extra left over and did my cub cadet headlight cover.

This product is as advertised and the process is explained well throughout the reviews.  Works well and makes a big difference in the overall appearance of vehicle.  Too soon to say if it will really last as long as I own the vehicle, but for now I am quite pleased with the results.  Highly recommend over other products.

I decided to try the Cerakote Ceramic Headlight Restoration Kit, and I was really impressed with how easy the process was and how great my headlights looked afterward! Even though the instructions say it’s a simple 30-minute job, it actually took me closer to an hour to clean and prep everything properly. I took my time after the rinse off because of the clear warnings about water and the final step, so I let the headlights dry overnight before finishing with the final step.Once I applied the ceramic coating, the results were amazing—my headlights looked like new! The kit is super easy to use, with no need for power tools, and the step-by-step process made it a breeze. If you're looking for something quick and effective to restore your headlights, this is definitely worth it. The fact that it’s supposed to last as long as I own the car is a huge plus!I will update in a couple years and let you know how it holds up.

I found these to be a good value. I have purchased several other brands of microfiber towels. These are the thickest and softest of those that I have tried.  They work beautifully on our stainless appliances. They also make a difference detailing the inside of our car. I got the gray and love that color option as it does not show any dirt and after washing they look brand new.

I love these small cloths. I use them in the kitchen and bathrooms to wipe up water on the countertops. They are very absorbent. The small size is great for small jobs. They wash and dry easily. They are soft and the gray color is a bonus for me.

These are fantastic absorbers and incredibly useful around the house, workplace, and even in your car. They’re super soft and do a great job of hiding dirt until it’s time to wash them. Highly recommended!—Koorosh

Was looking for a few towels to keep in my car as I like to use a few products for my car care. It does a good job and doesn't leave any scratches that I've noticed on my car. These don't necessarily wash well. Some residue might stick on after cleaning some components of your car. For the most part you should be okay. I was a little surprised at the size of the towels upon receiving them. They are a bit smaller then what the photos would show you. And not as thick too. But other than that they perform well. I wouldn't bout these with a tough job. But for a gentle wipe down (perfect for a car) these fit quite well. Money well spent.

The first one out of the package had me impressed. I didn't think it would be so absorbent even after reading all the comments, but this product definitely lives up to its reputation. I purchased the cloths in grey, mostly because of the price difference and I was going to give it a try. After the first week, I'm sold. This product does everything it claims and more. Very decently priced and worked very well. Easy to use and ability to relay to my mechanic. Worked recommend and purchase again.

This Item (Ancel AD310 OBD-11 scanner) is great for a first timer or a novice like myself, it is very simple to understand and operate and has helped me in situations many times when a scan was needed it felt good being able to do it myself, I am very satisfied with it, great tool it works well within its parameters.

Easy to use. Self explanatory when you plug it in. Easy to erase codes when they pop up. I was able to erase the O2 sensor code on my 2012 Ford Focus SE easily. Lots of other functions on this device as well. Nice quality. I recommend. Cheers

Works really well and easy to use. Not to heavy but very solid. Fills tire to selected level quickly even on my truck. The unit moves around a bit so placed it against tire to steady. Only complaint is that the gauges are placed flat in unit and the unit needs to be tilted back to see readings. It is very accurate and my TPMS reading matches the pressure reading on the inflator.

A recent slow leak prompted this purchase and I'm so happy I pulled the trigger. Being a DeWalt Dad meant I already had the batteries and am happy with the quality of their products. I was considering buying the AC adaptor, but unless you're inflating a lot of tires at one location, don't bother.  I haven't run the battery flat yet, so can't comment on the life, but the unit inflated my 17" tires by 5psi in around 20 seconds. Super easy to use and the brass fitting is threaded so no need to push and hold in place like those horrible gas stations hoses. Turn it on, attach hose, set PSI, push play button.  Auto shuts off when inflated.  It even gives you a half PSI over to account for unscrewing the fitting.  Genius! I can't believe I didn't buy one sooner. Knowing I save $2.50 with every use is so satisfying. Comes with attachments for other applications. Compact, sturdy, powerful, light weight, work horse. Buy it now.

Had this for almost 4 years now and I can say it's an absolute life and lung saver. I've used it on everything from tires to kids pools, balls, floats, mattresses etc.There is an added cost for the AC plug and, of course, batteries, and even a case of you want it need one. I got the AC plug and normally only use the car plug and not batteries. Battery use is okay but, understandably, they die quick if the voltage gets low or when they get hot.I keep this in my trunk along with a plug kit and it's been used hundreds of times for my tires. Where I work there's screws and nails always all over the place. This thing saves time and stress.

The DEWALT 20V MAX Tire Inflator has been an absolute game-changer for me. As someone who frequently travels and enjoys outdoor activities, having a reliable and portable tire inflator is essential, and this product delivers on every front.First and foremost, the compact and portable design is fantastic. It fits easily in my car's trunk without taking up much space, making it convenient to carry around. The build quality is what you'd expect from DEWALT – sturdy and durable, ensuring it can withstand regular use.One of the standout features is the automatic shut-off. This takes the guesswork out of inflating tires and gives me peace of mind knowing I won't overinflate. I simply set the desired pressure, and the inflator does the rest, shutting off automatically once the right pressure is reached. This feature is a real time-saver and adds a layer of safety.The LED light is another thoughtful addition. It’s incredibly useful for nighttime or low-light situations, making it easy to see what you're doing. This has already come in handy during a late-night tire issue, and it’s something I didn’t know I needed until I had it.Performance-wise, this inflator is impressive. Additionally, it’s versatile enough to handle other inflatables like sports balls and pool floats, thanks to the included adapters.One thing to note is that this is the bare tool only, so you’ll need to have a DEWALT 20V MAX battery and charger. The is a compact, well-made portable inflator. Quickly inflates car tires that are several pounds low, and I like that I can use my rechargeable batteries used in my other DEWALT tools. I’ve been using the HOTOR Trunk Organizer for a few months now, and it has been a game-changer for keeping my car neat and organized. The material feels durable and well-made, with a slightly textured surface that resists slipping, so items stay secure during drives. The foldable design is a huge plus—I can quickly tuck it away when I need more trunk space. It’s also super easy to clean, which is perfect for handling spills or dirt from outdoor gear. Overall, this organizer combines practicality with great build quality, making it a must-have for anyone who wants a tidy trunk!

This is a nice trunk organizer/organizer of your groceries. I put it in my trunk to hold odds and ends. It has a thick fabric, Nice pockets and areas to store smaller things . It’s nice and I could see using it for groceries. However, that’s not what I’m using it for so I may just buy another one to keep in my Trunk for groceries.

So I realize I don't exactly use this product as intended so let me start there.I bought this to put in the bed of my truck to keep the groceries from sliding around or escaping from their bags.  I really like it as it's convenient, has plenty of space, and even has side pockets and handles.  It definitely helps with keeping everything in one spot and has eliminated the groceries sliding around in the back.The cons - it's got Velcro straps that strap the compartments together but it's either they're all fully open or fully closed.  You cant  have it close just one compartment and use the other 2.  There's no reinforcement to the bottom.  Would be great to have a tougher or more heavy duty bottom.  And lastly I try to carry everything in one trip (hate unloading groceries and having to make 50 trips) so I tried the handles to see if I could carry it by myself in one trip loaded down with my haul from the store.  The straps held well enough but without a more sturdy bottom to it the organizer just folded like an accordion.  Again let me say I know this is not the intended use and purpose for this product but it does work well enough for what I am using it for.  I would definitely by it again or buy another one for our other cars.
Helps with car trunk organizer. Can hold a variety of items. Helps me to keep things in one place. Happy with the product. Can fold when not in use. Nice size.

The Good:The Velcro side strap are nice for shrinking to 2 or 1 compartment.  The netting is set up to separate more items into smaller pockets. Price is on the economy level. Compartments collapse down well. If you are never taking this out of your car, then it is probably worth it when you can get it on a discount.The Bad:The side walls and pockets are paper thin and flimsy, you most certainly don't get the padded and stiff side walls or pockets that are pictured.  When you go to move or shift anything, the entire compartment does an accordian-like shift due to there being no side support like in competitor items (see x-cosrack trunk organizer). The other big flaw is that the handles are only on the inside of the compartments on either end, so if you taper it down to 2 compartments and you bought a 3 compartment one, based on the weight, you may be in for a surprise when going to move something like heavy-ish groceries indoors.Conclusion:I'd spend an extra $10-15 on one of the nicer organizers that have small helpful extras like straps to keep the bags in place or small coolers. They aren't going to be anything overly impressive, but they may do things like keep bad fish and leftover smells from permeating the inside of your car if you can't make it straight home right away(Yes, this happened and I forgot until I opened that bag and was slapped across the face by smelly fried Cod).  Hope this helps!
